由牛二定律

$$ F = m \ddot u$$

### 求 $F$

作用力为两绳子的拉力

$$ F = -2T \cos \theta = 2T \frac{u}{\sqrt{u^2 + l^2}}$$

绳子拉力为

$$T = \sigma A + \overline T$$

应力

$$
\begin{align}
\sigma &amp;= E \varepsilon\\
&amp;= E \frac{\Delta l}{l} \\
\end{align}
$$

应变

$$\Delta l = \sqrt{u^2 + l^2} - l$$

代入则有

$$m\ddot u + \frac{2 \overline Tu}{{\sqrt {l^2 + u^2} }} + 2EAu\left( {\frac{1}{l} - \frac{1}{{\sqrt {l^2 + u^2} }}} \right)= 0$$"><h2>1</h2><p>由牛二定律</p><p></p><div class="MathJax" display="block" div.data-content:
## 1

由牛二定律

$$ F = m \ddot u$$

### 求 $F$

作用力为两绳子的拉力

$$ F = -2T \cos \theta = 2T \frac{u}{\sqrt{u^2 + l^2}}$$

绳子拉力为

$$T = \sigma A + \overline T$$

应力

$$
\begin{align}
\sigma &= E \varepsilon\\
&= E \frac{\Delta l}{l} \\
\end{align}
$$

应变

$$\Delta l = \sqrt{u^2 + l^2} - l$$

代入则有

$$m\ddot u + \frac{2 \overline Tu}{{\sqrt {l^2 + u^2} }} + 2EAu\left( {\frac{1}{l} - \frac{1}{{\sqrt {l^2 + u^2} }}} \right)= 0$$
div.p: 作用力为两绳子的拉力

div.data-content:
## 2

由泰勒展开

$$
\begin{cases}
\frac{u}{\sqrt {l^2+u^2}} &\approx u \\
\frac{u}{l} - \frac{u}{\sqrt {l^2+u^2}} &\approx \frac{u^3}{2 l^3}
\end{cases}
$$

代入则有

$$m\ddot u + \frac{{2\bar T}}{l}u\left( t \right) + \frac{{EA}}{{{l^3}}}u{\left( t \right)^3} = 0$$
